-align: center; width: 70%;"><em>Pew Survey</em></figcaption></figure></div=
><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;What happens,&#8221; they seem to ask, &#8220;if =
we let a bad idea slip through?&#8221;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The more import=
ant, and harder to predict, question is, &#8220;What happens if we choke th=
e good ideas out before they have a chance to sift down?&#8221;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">There&#8217;s good news though: the experimentation layer seems t=
o be getting unshackled. In my conversations and adventures on the internet=
, I&#8217;ve noticed the tide turning. Maybe you&#8217;ve felt the vibe shi=
ft, too.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">From the ashes of institutional trust a phoen=
ix of trust in people to make up their own minds is rising.&#160;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">Throwing everyone together, online, 24/7, and giving them infor=
mation and access to each other directly, unfiltered, was bound to have a j=
arring impact. It&#8217;s become clear that no one &#8211; not politicians,=
 not the smartest person you know &#8211; has all The Answers, and we&#8217=
;re learning how to live in a world where that&#8217;s evident.&#160;</p><p=
 style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">Instead of trust in any one person or group of people&#8217=
;s opinions at the experimentation layer, we can trust that the deeper laye=
rs will provide a backstop, and free the experimentation layer up for maxim=
al variance. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">A few examples: </p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><s=
pan>Controversial ideas aren&#8217;t as likely to get you canceled anymore.=
 The Overton Window seems to be expanding. Just this weekend, </span><a hre=
f=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/b5327252-6a04-47d0-9441-8b6f86cac11a?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Moment of Zen int=
erviewed Curtis Yarvin</a><span>. I don&#8217;t know Yarvin&#8217;s ideas w=
ell enough to say which I agree with and disagree with, but airing them out=
 and letting people decide which to incorporate and which to dismiss for th=
emselves feels like a healthy step. It&#8217;s been said before, but X unde=
r Elon has played a role here, and I think it&#8217;s a positive developmen=
t.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Crypto is coming back, using the=
 building blocks from the last cycle to create something about which Larry =
Fink, the head of world&#8217;s largest asset manager, BlackRock, said: &#8=
220;</span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/be864233-a656-4cc5-99c7=
-3ffbf7950b7b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Ex=
kRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">We=
 believe the next step going forward will be the tokenization of financial =
assets.</a><span>&#8221;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">People want the tokeni=
zation of financial assets, proof of personhood, and stablecoins without mo=
nkey jpegs, memecoins, and friend.tech, but I guess the point I&#8217;m try=
ing to make is that you don&#8217;t get the tokenization of financial asset=
s, proof of personhood, and stablecoins without monkey jpegs, memecoins, an=
d friend.tech.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This meme only ever makes sense w=
